zoolog:
Zooarcheological Analysis with Log-Ratios

2021-02-02

Introduction

The R package zoolog includes functions and reference data to generate and manipulate log-ratios (also known as log size index (LSI) values) from measurements obtained on zooarchaeological material. Log ratios are used to compare the relative (rather than the absolute) dimensions of animals from archaeological contexts. zoolog is also able to seamlessly integrate data and references with heterogeneous nomenclature, which is internally managed by a zoolog thesaurus.

Installation

You can install the released version of zoolog from CRAN with:

install.packages("zoolog", build_vignettes=TRUE)

And the development version from GitHub with:

install.packages("devtools")
library(devtools)
devtools::install_github("josempozo/zoolog@HEAD", build_vignettes = TRUE, force = TRUE)

Find more details in the zoolog documentation.
